text:
Found a kick butt solution for this based on what Stefen mentioned. Thought I’d share. You can embed the arrow as an svg as a dataURI and surprisingly it’s backward compatible.

select {
    background-image: url(’<https://cdn2.HubSpot.net/hubfs/36339/2018SW-template/Icons/selectbox-down-arrow.svg'>);
    background-image: url(‘data:image/svg+xml;utf8,&lt;svg xmlns=“http://www.w3.org/2000/svg” version=“1" viewBox=“0 0 255 128”&gt;&lt;path d=“M0 0l128 128L255 0z”/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;’);
    background-position: 97% 50%;
    background-size: 10px 10px;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    padding-right: 22px!important;
}
